ed to him His wife turned. The smile came out completely successfully. 'Ouf,'

sighed Mrs. Luzhin, 'we're finally rid of them,' and quickly embracing her husband, she began to kiss him — on the right eye, then the chin, then the left ear — observing a strict sequence that had once been approved by him. 'Well, cheer up, cheer up,' she repeated. 'That madam's gone away now, disappeared.' 'Disappeared,' said Luzhin obediently and with a sigh kissed the hand that was patting his neck.

